<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1783] Logical error in code for determining mode for opening of log files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1783</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a logical error in the following function in DirFile4.java&lt;br/&gt;
for determining which mode to use when opening a new log file:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    public StorageRandomAccessFile getRandomAccessFile( String mode) throws FileNotFoundException&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
{
        // Assume that modes &quot;rws&quot; and &quot;rwd&quot; are not supported.
        if(!rwsOK &amp;amp;&amp;amp; &quot;rws&quot;.equals( mode) || &quot;rwd&quot;.equals( mode))
            mode = &quot;rw&quot;;
        return new DirRandomAccessFile4( (File) this, mode);
    }
&lt;p&gt; // end of getRandomAccessFile&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The expression in the if test is missing parentheses around the OR&lt;br/&gt;
expression making it return the wrong value for one case. If &quot;rwd&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
mode is requested for the file (and this is supported by the JVM), the&lt;br/&gt;
file is opened with &quot;rw&quot; instead of &quot;rwd&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE: this bug does not effect any current Derby versions since as far&lt;br/&gt;
as I know &quot;rwd&quot; is never used for log files. I came across it when&lt;br/&gt;
experimenting with using &quot;rwd&quot; for the log.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>JVM 1.4.2 and later</environment>
